    <p>After a year <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/?lat=39.3076&amp;lon=-76.586&amp;zoom=14&amp;layers=B000FTF">holed up</a> trying to figure out my <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ikigai" title="raison d'Ãªtre">ikigai</a>, I'm ready for some movement. I've been working on possible plans for the summer. My dream at this point is to:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Finish a <a href="~/projects/thesis/">Masters thesis</a></li>
      <li>Create <a href="~/projects/events/Burning Man/2010/">art</a> for <a href="http://burningman.com">Burning Man</a></li>
      <li>Serve as a <a href="http://singinst.org"><acronym title="Singularity Institute for Artificial Intelligence">SIAI</acronym></a> <a href="http://singinst.org/aboutus/opportunities/visiting-fellow">summer fellow</a></li>
      <li>Program for <a href="http://code.google.com/soc/">Summer of Code</a></li>
      <li><a href="~/projects/events/wedding/">Wed</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Everything hinges on the art project idea. A project that uses interesting technology could be written up as a thesis. A project written in open source could be a part of Summer of Code. A project about humanity's long-term survival could appeal to the Singularity Institute. So, all I need is an interesting open source art project about the future that fits in the theme "<a href="http://burningman.com/art_of_burningman/bm10_theme.html">Metropolis</a>".</p>

    <img class="center" src="http://burningman.com/art_of_burningman/images/10_theme.jpg" alt="Burning Man 2010: Metropolis"/>

    <!--more-->

    <p>What I want to do is a <a href="http://www.lo-q.com">Flash Pass</a> bred with an <acronym title="artificial intelligence">AI</acronym>. You might have seen the Flash Pass or one of its cousins at your local amusement park. The idea is you get a list of what ride is available when, you make your reservation and when your time come you show up and ride.</p>

    <img class="borderless rowimage" src="~/sources/image/q-bot.png" alt="Flash Pass"/>

